<TEXT>
the permit process imposed on pueblo 
indians seeking eagle feathers for religious rites is 
unconstitutional a federal judge ruled 
the process constitutes excessive entanglement with the 
religious tenets of those tribes and is therefore an invalid mixture 
of church and state us district judge john conway ruled friday 
eagle feathers are available to pueblos only by applying to a 
depository maintained by the us fish and wildlife service 
conways ruling came in the case of mark suazo hinds a pueblo 
charged in the purchase of a golden eagle for 500 that he resold to 
a cousin the case stems from a fish and wildlife service sting that 
netted hundreds of arrests in colorado and new mexico in january 
the most significant thing to me in the opinion is that this 
court has recognized that indian religious practices are entitled to 
just as much protection as anybody elses religion said defense 
attorney john boyd 
us attorney bill lutz said he is unsure whether he will appeal 
but he said theres no question that the transfer of the eagle 
was for money and we dont think indian religious freedom was an 
issue 
hinds says he sold the eagle at no profit to his cousin who 
needed it after he was to be initiated into a pueblo religious 
society the cousin tried for two years to get an eagle through the 
federal depository the defense argued 
the prosecution contended that hinds bought the eagle to make a 
fetish for a nonindian psychiatrist for several thousand dollars 
but the judge ruled that the prosecution failed to establish any 
motive other than religious convictions 
the judge also noted that pueblos whose applications are granted 
get frozen eagles that often are killed by nonindians in an 
unspecified manner some indian rituals forbid use of a dead eagle 
others designate how the eagle should be killed he said 
alfonso ortiz a pueblo anthropologist testified at a hearing 
that pueblo religion would wither away without eagle feathers 
but that the plumes are available only through a cumbersome and 
intrusive process 
the federal depository has a special problem because one may 
apply but one never knows when or even if youll get the feathers 
you need he said its very sad that pueblo peoples who still 
practice their traditional religion have to rely on such a system 
