vulnerable structures 
preprations for individual coastal residents are much the same 
martin nelson a meteorologist at the national hurricane center 
said anyone in hugos path should stock up on nonperishable food 
flashlight batteries and drinking water and should make sure their 
car has plenty of gas 
boatowners should bring their vessels ashore if possible and 
residents closest to the water especially those in mobile homes 
should be ready to evacuate pet owners need to find places for 
their animals which usually arent allowed at evacuation shelters 
nelson had warnings for the socially minded and the adventurous 
he said those in the hurricanes path shouldnt plan hurricane 
parties and no one should venture outside if they are in the eye of 
a hurricane 
