londonbased financial times said the shakeout in junk bonds is the 
latest phase of a rolling liquidation that in past years had 
wrung speculation out of agriculture and the energy markets 
the secret is to shake out the speculators in batches not as 
in the 1920s all together buchan said 
james grant publisher of grants interest rate observer said he 
believed buchans assessment seemed on target its always good 
news when false values are exposed for being false he said in an 
interview 
