<TEXT>
financially crippled campeau corp today secured 
an emergency loan that will enable its department stores to pay 
debts but force the companys founder robert campeau to relinquish 
control 
campeaus problems caused largely by obligations on its junk 
bond debts had raised doubts about the future of his company and 
injected uncertainty into the 200 billion market in junk bonds 
which are highyield highrisk securities used to finance takeovers 
and expansion 
olympia amp york developments ltd which is providing the 250 
million loan also obtained the power to steer campeau through a 
major financial overhaul 
olympia amp york owned by torontos reichmann brothers will be 
given three seats on a new 10member campeau board and the right to 
buy almost 16 million shares of the canadian retail and property 
holding company 
the first portion of the loan from olympia amp york became 
available immediately campeau said in an announcement released by 
its toronto headquarters 
the agreement calls for up to 150 million to be channeled to 
campeaus federated department stores inc and the remainder to its 
allied stores corp division 
the money will allow the department store operators to meet 
interest payments now due on debts and to pay suppliers shipping 
merchandise ahead of the crucial christmas shopping season 
under the definitive agreement with olympia amp york a new board 
of directors was appointed the configuration of the board reflects 
the amount of power that chairman robert campeau relinguished in the 
company he built 
three members of the new board come from the campeau group three 
from olympia amp york and four represent minority shareholders 
the board formed a restructuring committee headed by one of the 
three reichmannappointed members of the board lionel dodd the 
committee intends to hire the investment banking firm merrill lynch 
amp co to help develop a restructuring plan and retail business 
consultants from mckinsey amp co also will be engaged 
robert campeau who retained the titles of chairman and chief 
executive officer said the companys us arm will employ a chief 
executive officer and chief financial officer whose main mission 
will be to supervise the restructuring of campeaus retail 
operations in the united states 
the two new executives who have yet to be selected will report 
directly to the board and the restructuring committee 
part of the restructuring includes the sale of the 17store 
bloomingdales chain which is part of federated 
olympia amp york will use its best efforts to arrange temporary 
financing of about 800 million until campeau can arrange for the 
sale of new yorkbased bloomingdales olympia amp york has agreed to 
put up some of the bridge loan if necessary 
for coming to campeaus rescue olympia amp york will receive 
warrants entitling it to purchase up to 15625 million ordinary 
campeau shares at 16 a piece until sept 18 1991 
added to its current 245 percent stake in campeau the purchase 
of 16 million additional shares would raise olympia amp yorks 
interest in campeau to 384 percent on a fully diluted basis 
robert campeaus stake would be cut to 432 percent from about 54 
percent under the agreement 
campeau common stock last traded at 1350 canadian dollars 
before it was halted last wednesday after trading as high as 2225 
a few days earlier 
commenting on the deal with olympia amp york robert campeau said 
after reviewing projected cash flow requirements and the financial 
position of campeau and its subsidiaries he determined that a major 
restructuring was needed to reduce leverage 
at my request olympia amp york has agreed to substantially 
increase its investment in campeau and to be primarily responsible 
for the refinancing and restructuring campeau said the 
significant experience and expertise of the olympia amp york 
organization will greatly assist in the endeavor 
